7\. On account of definite rule.

Another argument for our conclusion is that the text 'Doing works here
let a man desire to live a hundred years,' &c. (Is. Up. II), expressly
enjoins lifelong works on him who knows the Self. The general
conclusion, therefore, is that knowledge (meditation) is merely
auxiliary to works. Of this view the next Sûtra finally disposes.

